    <section class="page-section no-top-margin">
      <div class="panel">
        <span class="section-kicker">Article Focus</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Advanced AI and social impact</h2>
        <p class="section-text">
          This article explains how advanced AI, especially Artificial General Intelligence and
          Artificial Superintelligence, could create new divisions in society. It focuses on how
          people may disagree about which AI systems to trust, who controls them, and how much
          authority AI should have.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="page-section no-top-margin">
      <div class="panel">
        <span class="section-kicker">Summary</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Summary of the article</h2>
        <p class="section-text">
          The article explains that AGI and AI superintelligence may not automatically bring society
          together. Instead, powerful AI systems could create fragmentation because different groups
          may trust different AI tools, follow different AI-generated answers, or disagree about
          which system is correct.
        </p>
        <p class="section-text">
          A major point in the article is that the risk is not only the technology itself, but also
          how humans respond to it. If people begin treating AI as an ultimate authority,
          disagreements about control, ethics, responsibility, and trust may become more serious.
        </p>
        <p class="section-text">
          The article also connects advanced AI to broader social impacts such as political division,
          economic disruption, and changes in professional decision-making. It suggests that
          governance, accountability, and human oversight will be important as AI systems become more
          powerful and influential.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

